[{"id":"FT3407","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p><img alt=\"The figure shows a circle with six equally spaced radii drawn. The angle between adjacent radii is 60 degrees. Two of the radii are horizontal. The point on the circle at the end of the right horizontal radius is labelled 2 times uppercase M. The point at the end of the left horizontal radius is labelled lowercase m. The point at the end of the radius 60 degrees clockwise from the point labelled lowercase m is labelled uppercase M.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/ae3c3b19a1dfe97d64490fda561e85dd/original.png\"></p><p>A wheel of radius <em>R </em>and negligible mass is mounted on a horizontal frictionless axle so that the wheel is in a vertical plane. Three small objects having masses <em>m</em>, <em>M, </em>and 2<em>M</em>, respectively, are mounted on the rim of the wheel, as shown above. If the system is in static equilibrium, what is the value of <em>m </em>in terms of <em>M </em>?</p>","choicesHtml":["<span aria-label=\"cap m over 2\"><math> <semantics> <mrow> <mfrac> <mi>M</mi> <mn>2</mn> </mfrac> </mrow> <annotation encoding=\"MathType-MTEF\">MathType@MTEF@5@5@@3A0C@</annotation> </semantics> </math></span>","<p><em>M</em></p>","<span aria-label=\"3 cap m over 2\"><math> <semantics> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>3</mn> <mi>M</mi> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </mfrac> </mrow> <annotation encoding=\"MathType-MTEF\">MathType@MTEF@5@5@@3AC9@</annotation> </semantics> </math></span>","<p>2<em>M</em></p>","<span aria-label=\"5 cap m over 2\"><math> <semantics> <mrow> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>5</mn> <mi>M</mi> </mrow> <mn>2</mn> </mfrac> </mrow> <annotation encoding=\"MathType-MTEF\">MathType@MTEF@5@5@@3ACB@</annotation> </semantics> </math></span>"],"answer":1}]